FBIS4-35994 "drnes108_r_94003" FBIS-NES-94-108 Daily Report 4 Jun 1994 India Government Successfully Launches Prithvi Missiles Government Successfully Launches Prithvi Missiles Second Test Scheduled BK0406160094 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1530 GMT 4 Jun 94 BK0406160094 Delhi All India Radio Network English BFN [Text] The users trial for the surface-to-surface missile, Prithvi, began today with the successful launch of the missile from the interim test range near Balasore in Orissa. The indigenously built missile soared into clear sky at 1144 [0614 GMT] hitting the built-up target in (Tentulichura) island of Bhadrak Coast in Bay of Bengal. Defense Ministry officials said today's launch fully met the mission's requirements. The 150-to-250-km-range missile was launched from a mobile platform in the presence of senior officials of the Indian Army and the Defense Research and Development Organization, DRDO. The second trial will be conducted on Monday [6 June] with a target in the high seas which will be followed by other trials in battlefield conditions. Prithvi is one of the five missiles developed under DRDO's integrated missile development program. The other four are Agni, Trishul, Akash and Nag.
